HEADWORD: Fasti
<hw>Fas"ti</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The Roman calendar, which gave the days for festivals,
courts, etc., corresponding to a modern almanac.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Records or registers of important events.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fastidiosity</ent>⟦br⟧
